The paper discusses an analyzer and optimizer for logic programs, which falls under the category of programming languages and compilers. Specifically, it focuses on the use of abstract interpretation and tabled constraint logic programming, which are topics related to programming language semantics and logic. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper mentions fixpoint computation, which is a topic related to logic and set theory, suggesting that cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses performance evaluation and optimization, which are topics related to software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions branch switching and resumption, which are topics related to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
